## 9. How the Variables Map

The five variables identified during analysis map exactly to the layers:

| Variable | Layer | In the equation |
|----------|-------|-----------------|
| Current state | L1 (Body) | θ(t) — angular position now |
| Previous state | L1→L3 | dθ/dt — velocity of change |
| Direction | L4 (Self) | sign of dθ/dt — toward experience or measurement? |
| Depth | L3→L5 | d²θ/dt² — acceleration of the process |
| Uncertainty | β | θ_cube ± β — you never arrive exactly at center |

They are not new variables. They are the layers themselves, seen in motion.

