## 12. What Changed Conceptually

### Before (UCF v3.0)

- `C_total` = "how coherent you are now" — a photograph
- The system could be "centered" and dead
- Equilibrium = being at 11.09°
- Time was external to the formula

### After (UCF v3.1)

- `C_total(t)` = trajectory of coherence — a movie
- A living system is never still
- Equilibrium = oscillating AROUND 11.09°
- Time emerges from the traversal of the layers
- If θ doesn't change → the system is dead

### What the "dead system" bug revealed

The stability test `test_both_engines_zero_for_dead_system` showed that the OmegaEngine returned 0.438 instead of 0.0 when all activations were zero. This wasn't a code error — it was the formula saying: **a system can have base coherence factors (α/S × R) without being alive.** Structure exists without movement. But structure without movement is not coherence — it's a corpse.

The dynamic equation resolves this: if `dθ/dt = 0` and `d²θ/dt² = 0`, the system is not oscillating. It is dead. Regardless of what `C_total` says.

**Life is not a value. Life is oscillation.**

